tags: good luck corralling both kids Vader
body:
Fic Prompts: Star Wars Wednesday

(In which Vader Down ends a little differently…also a loose continuation of an old prompt where Aphra found out by accident – and via nosy droids – that Leia was genetically related to Luke)

The shuttle was coming down too fast.

Darth Vader watched it fall, realized the impact was going to trap the passengers inside. And the boy- he was in danger of injury. There was no way Karbin’s men would think to secure their prisoner in crash webbing. He had a few options: he could use the Force to ease the ship’s landing, and then he’d have to kill the guards. Or he could use the Force to shield Luke alone, and hope the impact was enough to kill the others.

The girl was nearby, he could sense her now that he knew what to look for. Strange that she had always remained so camouflaged. It seemed to be instinct, which he could admit to finding as impressive as the boy’s skill as a pilot. Had the Alderaanians known? Had it been a conspiracy before or after Padme-

No.

Now was not the time to think of such things. Later, when he had them – twins?! – safe and secluded, out of reach of Cylo’s mad apprentices. When he had ensured that both his rivals were ashes and his…children…were unable to slip out of his grasp, then he would have all the time in the world to contemplate the depths of Palpatine’s treachery.

Vader caught hold of the shuttle with the Force, and brought it down with a slight change of angle. It still landed hard, and he knew he would have to check the boy for injury. He didn’t sense anything serious, but there was certainly pain. Better that way: once he acquired the boy, speed would be of the essence. There would be a limited window of time to capture the princess and sequester them safely away from prying eyes before he had to return to his “master”.

The red glow of his lightsaber cast strange shadows across the sand as he marched down to tear the hatch open. He would be careful. Aphra would not know about this part of his plan. There was always a chance of betrayal when one was dealing with Sith or their associates, and so he would wait to involve Skywalker and the Princess until he could be sure the cards would fall in his favor.

Two of the guards struggled to their feet, angry and confused. Darth Vader would have curled his lip at them if he could have.

“I’ve come to retrieve young Skywalker,” he announced flatly.

summary: Good day. I have always enjoyed reading your views on the SW fandoms blind willfulness to ignorance. With your message to Jason...
question: Good day. I have always enjoyed reading your views on the SW fandoms blind willfulness to ignorance. With your message to Jason Fry, and what he said. I am beginning to think episode IX will not have a romance. Rey will be single and they will pair Finn with Rose or some crap. To avoid the whole fandom drama with an interracial couple. This will be the 1st SW movie with no main romance, cowardly as it will be. What's are your thoughts on that possibility.
answer:
I think it’s possible. With JJ at the wheel, I don’t think either Finn or Rey will have an endgame romance with anyone else, but I think it’s possible that it ends like the first Pacific Rim, where Mako and Raleigh were together, but there’s no kiss or overt proof of romance.

I hated the ambiguity of Mako/Raleigh in PR, because it called to mind the ‘90s Hollywood movies starring Chow Yun Fat and Jet Li, where they could be heroes, but they couldn’t kiss the girl (not just the white girl – Jet Li’s kiss with Aaliyah in Romeo Must Die was cut because it made test audiences uncomfortable. Romeo Must Die was a modern retelling of Romeo and Juliet, but test audience didn’t like the idea of a Chinese Romeo and a Black Juliet kissing). Or, more directly, Will Smith iRobot and I am Legend.

I think it’s more likely that Finn and Rey get a “safe” ambiguous ending together than an ending that shoots down Finnrey completely. I do think that would be cowardly. I don’t think it’s something JJ is afraid of – he unapologetically brought Spuhura to the screen even though it was an unpopular move with fans, including a huge number of passionate Spirk shippers. But, of course, JJ won’t have the last word.

The first two trilogies ended with hope for the future far more than romance. Both ended with Luke and Leia, and I think Luke and Leia will have a place in the ending of ix. The hope for the future, though, is Finn and Rey. It’s more important to me that Finn’s importance is made clear than anything else.
